IBADAN – No fewer than 5,000 members of the Action Democratic Congress (ADC) drawn across the 33 local government areas of Oyo State on Friday expressed their support for Governor Seyi Makinde in his second term bid as governor launched his campaign. Led by the former senator, representing Oyo Central Senatorial District, Senator Momsurat Sumonu, ADC members said Makinde had fulfilled his agreement with the coalition partners. According to Sunmonu who briefed journalists after the thank you rally and visit the Governor, Makinde accommodated many of the ADC members in his government. Ukrainian President Downplays Talk Of Russian Invasion 10 Injured In Pittsburgh Bridge Collapse According to her, “We are here to appreciate the governor because he kept his promise to us in ADC. When we started this coalition, people said Makinde won’t compensate us. But today, Makinde had fulfilled his agreement with us. Despite maintaining the name of our party. “A lot of ADC members were accommodated in this present government, our members are Commissioners, Special Advisers (SAs), Local Government Chairman’s.” Appreciating their thank you visit,  Seyi Makinde urged aggrieved members of the coalition to have a rethink, saying there are many things to benefit from the government. He also used the avenue to tell supporters the introductory song that will be their trademark during the electioneering ahead of the 2023 election. A chieftain of the party who was appointed as special adviser to the governor,  Hon. Gbenga Oyekola said: “Are here to thank the governor. He said there were vehicles to convey members but there was no money to pay them. POLL “We are getting things you are all sending to us. Many people left our party because they cannot endure. I am thanking the governor on behalf of all the ADC appointees for what the governor had done for us.”